{{italic title}}
{{Refimprove|date=December 2011}}
'''''Contrails''''' is a small handbook issued to new cadets entering the [[United States Air Force Academy]]. It contains information on [[United States Air Force]] and [[United States military]] history; Academy history;<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.usafatoday.org/wiki/index.php/Contrails|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090108052000/http://www.usafatoday.org/wiki/index.php/Contrails|archivedate=January 8, 2009|accessdate=December 9, 2011|title=Contrails|publisher=USAFAToday.org}}</ref> [[List of United States Air Force Academy alumni|notable Academy graduates]]; aircraft, satellites, and munitions in the current U.S. Air Force inventory; transcripts of important national documents such as the [[Preamble to the United States Constitution|Preamble to the Constitution]] and the [[Star-Spangled Banner|full national anthem]]; and famous quotes, which are usually patriotic or leadership-related.  Cadets in their fourth class ([[freshman]]) year are expected to learn most of the information from ''Contrails'', and be able to recite much of it verbatim. ''Contrails'' has traditionally been published in the class color—Blue, Silver, Red, or Gold—of the freshman class.

